-- Perrigo Falls Most in 3 Months, Tracking Drop in Its U.S. Shares
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-02-12T10:36:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-12/perrigo-falls-most-in-3-months-tracking-drop-in-its-u-s-shares.html
Perrigo Co. (PRGO)  declined the most in
more than three months following a drop in the U.S. traded
shares last week.  The  shares  fell 4.6 percent, the biggest intraday decline
since Oct. 30, to 349 shekels, or the equivalent of $93.79, at
12:21 p.m. in  Tel Aviv . The stock closed at $93.31 in New York
on Feb. 10.  The Tel Aviv Stock Exchange opened today for the first time
since Feb. 7 after a general strike.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
